---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | PDFTwin"
  description="How PDFTwin handles your files, account data, and browser storage."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        PDFTwin is a browser-based file conversion workspace. We designed the service so routine
        document processing does not require storing your files on our servers permanently.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Files you upload</h2>
      <p>
        Server-side tools process files in memory and discard them after the request completes.
        We do not use uploaded documents to train AI models or build marketing lists.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Compare PDF tool renders documents locally in your browser using PDF.js. Those files
        are not uploaded for viewing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Browser workspace storage</h2>
      <p>
        The workspace file tray stores files in your browser using IndexedDB so you can switch
        tools without re-uploading. This data stays on your device until you clear it or remove
        site data from your browser.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Account preview data</h2>
      <p>
        Preview sign-in stores account details in your browser localStorage. When live account
        services are enabled, authentication will move to a dedicated provider with proper
        security controls.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We may use privacy-focused analytics on the production site to understand traffic and
        improve reliability. Analytics providers do not receive the contents of your uploaded
        files.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy can be sent through the contact options listed on
        <a href="https://pdftwin.com">pdftwin.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
